Home    /    People    /    Faculty    /    Robert Kooima 






Robert Kooima
Assistant Professor



2016 Digital Media Center



Louisiana State University
Baton Rouge, LA 70803




Phone: 225 578 7150 / 225 578 9483 

kooima@csc.lsu.edu

Educational Background
Ph.D. in Computer Science, University of Illinois at Chicago, 2008M.S. in Computer Science, Universtiy of Iowa, 2001
 
Research Interests
Real Time Computer Graphics, Interactive Display Technology, Digital Imaging, Image Processing
 
Teaching Responsibilities
CSC 4357: Applied Computer GraphicsCSC 4356: Interactive Computer GraphicsCSC 4263: Video Game DesignCSC 2700: Digital Media Programming
 
Selected Publications
R. Kooima and D. Roberts. Rendering Planetary Terrains Using Heterogenous Data Sets, in Proceedings of the 21st International Planetarium Society Conference, 2012
M. SubbaRao, G. Gyuk, J. Fornek, and R. Kooima. Launching a Fulldome Camera Rig to Near Space, in Proceeding of  the 21st International Planetarium Society Conference, 2012
R. Kooima, A. Prudhomme, J. Schulze, D. Sandin and T. DeFanti. A Multi-viewer Tiled Autostereoscopic Virtual Reality Display, in Proceedings of the 17th ACM Symposium on Virtual Reality Software and Technology, 2010
J. Ge, R. Kooima, and A. Hutanu. High-Resolution Remote Visualization of Ray-Casted Volume Rendering on GPU Cluster. Poster, International Conference of High Performance Computing, Network, Storagea and Analysis, 2010
J. Ge, A. Hutanu, C. Toole, R. Kooima, I. Hossain and G. Allen. An Experimental Distributed Visualization System for Peta-scale Computing, Computing in Science & Engineering, vol. 12, no. 5, pp. 87-82, 2010
 
